        <div class="czx-faq-wrap">
          <div class="czx-reveal" style="display:grid; gap:12px;">
            <details class="czx-faq">
              <summary class="czx-faq__q">
                <span style="display:flex; gap:10px; align-items:center;">
                  <span class="czx-topic czx-topic--tech">Technology</span>
                  <span>Does it remove TDS from water?</span>
                </span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down czx-chevron"></i>
              </summary>
              <div class="czx-faq__a">
                No. Corzin is a salt-free conditioner, not an RO. It reduces hardness minerals’ tendency to form scale,
                but retains minerals and avoids water wastage.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="czx-faq">
              <summary class="czx-faq__q">
                <span style="display:flex; gap:10px; align-items:center;">
                  <span class="czx-topic czx-topic--source">Water Source</span>
                  <span>Is it suitable for borewell water?</span>
                </span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down czx-chevron"></i>
              </summary>
              <div class="czx-faq__a">
                Yes. Corzin is designed for high-hardness borewell and tanker water. A free water test helps choose the right model for your hardness level.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="czx-faq">
              <summary class="czx-faq__q">
                <span style="display:flex; gap:10px; align-items:center;">
                  <span class="czx-topic czx-topic--maint">Maintenance</span>
                  <span>How often do I need to change the media?</span>
                </span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down czx-chevron"></i>
              </summary>
              <div class="czx-faq__a">
                Typically 3–5 years depending on usage and hardness. No monthly salt refilling.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="czx-faq">
              <summary class="czx-faq__q">
                <span style="display:flex; gap:10px; align-items:center;">
                  <span class="czx-topic czx-topic--tech">Technology</span>
                  <span>Does it require electricity?</span>
                </span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down czx-chevron"></i>
              </summary>
              <div class="czx-faq__a">
                No. It works without electricity, so it also works during power cuts.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="czx-faq">
              <summary class="czx-faq__q">
                <span style="display:flex; gap:10px; align-items:center;">
                  <span class="czx-topic czx-topic--maint">Maintenance</span>
                  <span>Does it need salt refilling?</span>
                </span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down czx-chevron"></i>
              </summary>
              <div class="czx-faq__a">
                Never. That’s one of the biggest advantages over traditional salt-based softeners.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="czx-faq">
              <summary class="czx-faq__q">
                <span style="display:flex; gap:10px; align-items:center;">
                  <span class="czx-topic czx-topic--service">Usage</span>
                  <span>Does it work for the entire house?</span>
                </span>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down czx-chevron"></i>
              </summary>
              <div class="czx-faq__a">
                Yes. Installed at the overhead tank (or main inlet), it conditions water for all taps, showers, and appliances.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details class="czx-faq">
              <summary class="czx-faq__q">
